After a long wait for construction to finally be completed, I was able to come up to Zen here for their first opening.
It's a mid-sized place, nicely styled inside, & they're featuring 90-some main food items on the buffet.
I took my place in a comfortable booth, & started with their Won Ton Soup, which was delicious, & then some of their tasty, made-while-you-watch sushi.
Overall, the food items offered today were similar to the other Valley Chinese buffets that have a similar number of choices, & I enjoyed every dish I tried.
Some of my favorites were Stuffed Scallops on the Half-shell, tender & tasty Calamari, Chinese Peas sauteed with scallops, & tender, tasty boneless baby back ribs.
The desserts were excellent too, including the rich, delicious soft-serve ice cream.
Everything was served at the proper temperature, the staff was lovely, & things ran very smoothly... no small feat for a large business like this dealing with a good crowd of customers in to try it in its very first hour of business!
While more expensive than the wonderful Great Wall Chinese Buffet down the street, & not as huge & amazing as Zen in Chandler, I think this new place is a winner too, & I'll be returning.
A big welcome & 4 1/2-Stars for Zen Buffet, Glendale!
Lunch Buffet $7.59, $6.83 Sr.

I was able to get to this new place a few days after open.
The food was good, I was impressed with the sushi.
The staff waiting on me where very good to take plates and refill drinks.
The Decor is very basic but the food was presented well and they maintained the food freshness.
So the food made up for the simple decor, but I do recommend this buffet if you are ever in the area.

