This place just opened a few months, I was so impressed by Zen's buffet in Chandler,  a few friends and I decided to check this out also.
At a glance, it is pretty typical of another Chinese super buffet; large varieties of everything, very good selection.
However, when compare to the one in Chandler, This Zen is definitely two steps behind.
Since this is new, it is clean, it is expected.
I've noticed many dishes are "deep fried" rather than "Stir fried", I also noticed, many dishes are SOAK - BATH in oil.
Far more so than other Chinese buffets I've been to ( greasy, that's the word I was looking for).
Other than too GREASEEEY, it is pretty much the same as other Chinese buffets.
I ate heavenly on the Salad and desert section, it is very fresh - no grease.
Over all its not too bad, just don't set your expectation hi, don't look for anything new,  or exciting.
What you will find is  a typical Chinese buffet  food.

Yesterday, friend Iain B. asked me if I still like Zen here.
I hadn't been in since opening day, March 17th, & it has picked up a couple of low reviews, so I headed back for lunch today to see how it's doing.
I came after the lunch rush too, to try & catch Zen at it's worst, & here's how today's visit went for me:  I settled into a comfortable booth, & started with Hot & Sour Soup, which was good, & there was a bowl of chives there next to it, to sprinkle in if you like, which I thought that was a nice touch.
Browsing around, I noted that every serving tray had plenty of food in it, & an employee was staying right on top of keeping things cleaned up as the good crowd of diners were all eagerly scooping away.
My salad was above average, because there were tasty peanuts available to add in (ala Great Dragon & Great Wall II), & the Sesame Ginger Dressing was different & good.
In fact, I found ALL the food to be good here today, & here were a few standout items:  *  The Egg Foo Young, made right, & with the right gravy.
No "hockey pucks" here!
*  The tasty Bok Choy, cooked just enough in a delicious, buttery fish juice!
*  The Salt & Pepper Shrimp, much better than it sounds!
*  The Vanilla soft-serve ice cream (with cones available)...  rich & tasty!
The service was very friendly too.
So fine, this isn't an "amazing" buffet such as Pacific Seafood or Jen (or the one that will open in the old Hometown building at Bell & the 17 in July!
), but I think it deserves its turn for your Chinese buffet outings along Bell Rd.
here, along with Great Wall (5905), Shanghai (4201), New Super China (601 W), & little China Garden (cr.
of 19th Av).
Each one has special features of its own to offer, & I'll place Zen here a half-Star below my current favorite of these right now, Great Wall.
It's just fine really, & I think it certainly deserves better than the 2 1/2-Star average Yelp rating it's getting right now.

