I am generally not a fan of buffets.
I tend to eat more than I need.
We drive by this location several times a week and decided to see what it was like.
I was surprised.
I sampled small proportions of most of what was offered.
I started with the sushi.
The Ahi and Salmon was tender and tasty.
The pieces were small.
Remember this is a buffet not a sushi restaurant.
The quality of the sushi was surprisingly good.
Now for the rest of the food.
It was hot, plentiful, and tasted good.
They have a good variety, from frog legs to pizza.
The restaurant was clean and everyone was exceptionally nice.
If your glass started to get low someone was there to fill it.
Dirty plates were picked up quickly.
If you are into buffets I don't see how you could be disappointed.
Would I recommend?
Yes.
Would I go back.
Yes.
Most people go to a buffet to eat lots of food.
Zen Buffet has that.
Lots of food and quality was good.
So why did I give it 3 stars and not 4?
I will never be a fan of a buffet.

This was NOT worth my time or money.
The food tastes bad.
I've had a lot better food at other buffets in Phoenix, but that isn't saying much either!
The Panda Buffet near Lake Pleasant & Deer Valley is a lot better as far as buffets go.
I will not be going back!

